BRIEFING: DEPT GATE: B2 / ARR GATE: A3 (GATE(S) ARE SUBJECT TO CHANGE) PAX COUNTS: F 15 / Y 150 / NR 16 (PAX COUNTS ARE PRELIMINARY)
KSLC: MOSTLY CLEAR CONDITIONS INTO SUNDAY. CLOUDS WILL INCREASE EARLY AS A WEAK STORM SYSTEM APPROACHES FROM THE NORTHWEST. BROKEN TO OVERCAST CONDITIONS IN VFR RANGE ARE LIKELY MUCH OF THE DAY. SOUTHEAST WINDS WILL TRANSITION TO NORTHWEST AROUND 21Z.
ENRTE: EXPECT POSSIBLE AT DEPT. A WEST TO EAST JTST ACROSS THE LENGTH OF THE PACIFIC BEGINS TO EFFECT FLTS W130 TO W145 HEADING ACROSS TRACKS. EXPECT POSSIBLE TURB FOR ABOUT 30 MIN FROM EEP.
HAWAIIAN ISLANDS: A COMBINATION OF EASTERLY WINDS AND SEA BREEZES WILL AFFECT EACH ISLAND ON SUNDAY WITH CLOUDS BUILDING OVER MOUNTAIN AND INTERIOR SECTIONS IN THE AFTERNOON HOURS.
THREAT SPACE WEATHER: NONE
NOTAMS PLEASE REVIEW NOTAMS SECTION OF PACKET FOR MOST CURRENT INFORMATION
